803/* Analog to Digital Converter (ADC) */
804/* */
805/******************************************************************************/
806/******************** Bits definition for ADC_ISR register ******************/
807#define ADC_ISR_EOCAL_Pos (11U)
808#define ADC_ISR_EOCAL_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_EOCAL_Pos)
809#define ADC_ISR_EOCAL ADC_ISR_EOCAL_Msk
810#define ADC_ISR_AWD_Pos (7U)
811#define ADC_ISR_AWD_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_AWD_Pos)
812#define ADC_ISR_AWD ADC_ISR_AWD_Msk
813#define ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos (4U)
814#define ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos)
815#define ADC_ISR_OVR ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk
816#define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ_Pos (3U)
817#define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_EOSEQ_Pos)
818#define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ ADC_ISR_EOSEQ_Msk
819#define ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos (2U)
820#define ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos)
821#define ADC_ISR_EOC ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk
822#define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos (1U)
823#define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos)
824#define ADC_ISR_EOSMP ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk
825#define ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Pos (0U)

7808/* For a painless codes migration between the STM32L0xx device product */
7809/* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
7810/* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
7811/* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
7812/* product lines within the same STM32L0 Family */
7813/******************************************************************************/

7828#define AES_RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler

7830#define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
